John Lewis Plans to Open 10 Stores in Next Five Years, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-22T00:36:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/john-lewis-plans-to-open-10-stores-in-next-five-years-ft-says.html
John Lewis  Partnership Plc plans to
open 10 stores in city centers across the U.K. during the next
five years, the FT reported, citing Commercial Director Andrea
O’Donnell. The expansion, beginning with a new store in Exeter
next year, will help the retailer double its turnover from 3
billion pounds to 6 billion pounds over the following 10 years,
O’Donnell said, according to the FT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 